<mujoco model="K1">
  <!--
    Vendored from BoosterRobotics/booster_assets (BSD-3-Clause), commit
    486da0f864016676de6dab724fd60a8a551655d1, robots/K1/K1_22dof.xml.
    See VENDORED.md for full provenance. Local modifications made for the
    NUSim (see VENDORED.md "Local modifications" for detail):
      1. Converted the trunk's `<joint type="free">` root into an explicit
         `<freejoint name="root"/>` (upstream already rooted the trunk with a
         free joint; this just names it and uses the canonical MJCF idiom).
      2. Removed worldbody scene dressing (skybox texture, checker
         "texplane" texture + "matplane" material, the "ground" plane geom,
         and the two ad-hoc worldbody lights) so this file is a pure robot
         (body tree + assets + actuator + sensor + default) that can be
         <include>-d into a scene file without a duplicate floor/lighting.
      3. Added <accelerometer> and <velocimeter> sensors on the "imu" site,
         alongside the upstream framequat + gyro.
      4. Added a <keyframe> section with "ready", "lying_front" and
         "lying_back" poses for spawning/getup testing.
      5. Raised the 12 leg motor forceranges to the Booster actuator catalog
         effort limits used by the mujoco_playground K1 training model
         (hip pitch/roll/yaw 68/76/38.3, knee 112, ankle 38.3 N*m) so the RL
         walk policy is not torque-clamped below what it trained with.
  -->
