            just in front of the Head_2 face mesh (front face vertices reach
            x~=0.063 at this height; verified via the mesh's own STL bounds),
            centred laterally (y=0) at the vertical mid-point of the front face
            plate (z~=0.089, mesh z-range there is [0.049, 0.129]). xyaxes picks
            the camera's local X/Y axes directly in the Head_2 (=body, at head
            yaw/pitch=0) frame: X=(0,-1,0) is image-right = the robot's right
            (left is +Y here), Y=(0,0,1) is image-up = world-up when the head is
            level; the implied Z = X x Y = (-1,0,0) puts the view direction
            (-Z) at body +X, i.e. straight ahead -- this repo's own convention,
            confirmed three ways: the kickoff keyframe's comment ("rotation 0
            => facing +x"), the feet's toe-forward geometry (foot box offset
            +x), and Left/Right arm y-signs (left=+y). fovy=70 (vertical) gives
            a ~86 deg horizontal FOV at 4:3 -- a modest, ZED-mini-ish wide view;
            verified level/forward with an offscreen render (host MuJoCo, EGL)
            of this exact camera at the "ready" keyframe: horizon centred,
            floor/sky split behaves exactly as predicted from cam_xpos/cam_xmat.
          -->
